Get up to Speed on Mg!! Here are five popular types of magnesium, their uses, and potential side effects: 1.Magnesium Citrate Commonly used as a laxative for relieving constipation and sometimes recommended for improving digestion. It's also used to increase magnesium levels in people with deficiencies. I typically recommend the CitroMag for constipation - works great with tons of water and a tablet of dulcolax!;) Side effects: Diarrhea, stomach cramping, and dehydration if overused as a laxative. 2. Magnesium Oxide: Uses: Often taken as a supplement to prevent magnesium deficiency. Also used to relieve heartburn and indigestion. Lots of brands out there! Side effects: Upset stomach, nausea, and diarrhea. Not the most easily absorbed form of magnesium, so it might not be the best for raising magnesium levels. 3. Magnesium Glycinate and Byclycinate Uses: Known for its calming effects, this form is often recommended for sleep issues, anxiety, and muscle relaxation. Itâ€™s also gentler on the stomach than some other forms. I like the one by AOR Side effects: Generally well-tolerated, but mild stomach upset or diarrhea can occur in higher doses. 4. Magnesium Malate Uses: Often used for muscle pain, fatigue, and fibromyalgia due to its potential energy-boosting properties. Itâ€™s also good for replenishing magnesium levels. Side effects: Can cause digestive upset, including nausea and diarrhea, particularly in high doses. 5. Magnesium Threonate Uses: Gaining popularity for its ability to cross the blood-brain barrier, this form is often used to support cognitive function and memory. Keep you sharp!! Side effects: Headaches, drowsiness, and, in some cases, digestive upset.

                                                                    Get up to Speed on Mg!! Here are five popular types of magnesium, their uses, and potential side effects: 1.Magnesium Citrate Commonly used as a laxative for relieving constipation and sometimes recommended for improving digestion. It's also used to increase magnesium levels in people with deficiencies. I typically recommend the CitroMag for constipation - works great with tons of water and a tablet of dulcolax!;) Side effects: Diarrhea, stomach cramping, and dehydration if overused as a laxative. 2. Magnesium Oxide: Uses: Often taken as a supplement to prevent magnesium deficiency. Also used to relieve heartburn and indigestion. Lots of brands out there! Side effects: Upset stomach, nausea, and diarrhea. Not the most easily absorbed form of magnesium, so it might not be the best for raising magnesium levels. 3. Magnesium Glycinate and Byclycinate Uses: Known for its calming effects, this form is often recommended for sleep issues, anxiety, and muscle relaxation. Itâ€™s also gentler on the stomach than some other forms. I like the one by AOR Side effects: Generally well-tolerated, but mild stomach upset or diarrhea can occur in higher doses. 4. Magnesium Malate Uses: Often used for muscle pain, fatigue, and fibromyalgia due to its potential energy-boosting properties. Itâ€™s also good for replenishing magnesium levels. Side effects: Can cause digestive upset, including nausea and diarrhea, particularly in high doses. 5. Magnesium Threonate Uses: Gaining popularity for its ability to cross the blood-brain barrier, this form is often used to support cognitive function and memory. Keep you sharp!! Side effects: Headaches, drowsiness, and, in some cases, digestive upset.
